meta {
  name: Ready
  type: http
  seq: 2
}

get {
  url: {{module_base}}/ready.php
  auth: none
}

assert {
  res.status: isDefined
  res.body.status: isDefined
  res.body.db: isDefined
}

docs {
  Unauthenticated, redacted readiness (ARCHITECTURE.md §3.4/§3.7, R6). Runs
  genuine dependency probes and returns status enums only — no latencies, no
  config, no PHI. Shape:

    { "status": "ready|not-ready", "db": "ok|unreachable",
      "trace_store": "ok|unwritable", "llm": "ok|unreachable|circuit-open|unknown",
      "worker": "ok|stale|unknown", "breaker": "open|closed|unknown" }

  HTTP 200 when ready, 503 when not-ready (a DB/trace-store failure). LLM-down
  or breaker-open is degraded-but-serving — still 200 "ready", honestly
  reported (I6). Per-IP rate-limited: a burst may return 429 "rate-limited".
}
